properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 3 at 4:00AM PST until January 4 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected above 2000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of 4 to 8 inches between 2000 and 3000 feet, 8 to 12 inches in
between 3000 to 4000 feet and 10 to 18 inches in the higher
elevations.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains of Whatcom and Skagit Counties,
including the Mount Baker Ski Area. Cascade mountains of
Snohomish and King Counties, including Stevens and Snoqualmie
Pass and Cascade mountains of Pierce and Lewis Counties,
including Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 4 PM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult in the passes overnight
into Saturday.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 PM PST SATURDAY ABOVE 2000 FEET
